Defendant Terry A Molkentine in court with attorney Rebecca Coffee for Atty Craig Mastantuono.  Nicholas Steven Cerwin appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case calendared for a plea hearing.   Defendant  advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms; also defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense

Defendant Terry A Molkentine in court.  Marissa Luz Santiago appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Indigency Hearing conducted.    Indigency Hearing proceeded. Statements by the Defendant.  Based upon review of the Defendant's  statements made in court, the Court finds that the Defendant is indigent and does qualifiy for representation at the County's expense.   The court appointed Attorney Craig Mastantuono to represent the defendant at the rate of $60.00 per hour.  The attorney's bill is limited to a maximum of $6,000.00 - unless the Court grants additional approval;  Attorney Mastantuono out of the office until the end of this week.  Court notified of same and continues to appoint Attorney Mastantuno.   Defendant given business card for Attorney Mastantuno and instructed to contact Attorney Mastantuno next week.  Defendant to repay the County at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing on 5-1-2016 and to continue monthly payments until paid in full.  Nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment.   Order for appointment of counsel signed and filed and forwarded to Attorney Mastantuono along with notice that this matter is scheduled for a Preliminary Hearing.  Matter transferred back for a Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 16, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
